📌 Problem Statement

Hospital readmissions within 30 days increase operational costs and impact patient outcomes. 
This project aims to predict 30-day readmission risk using patient demographic, clinical, and operational data, and segment patients into risk groups.

📊 Dataset

3,000 patient records

Features: demographics, treatment metrics, cost, satisfaction

Target: readmitted_30d (0/1)

🛠 Tools & Technologies

Python (pandas, scikit-learn, seaborn)

SQL (MySQL)

Logistic Regression

Random Forest

K-Means Clustering

Power BI / Tableau (optional)

🔍 Project Workflow

SQL-based exploratory analysis

EDA & Feature Engineering

Logistic Regression & Random Forest modeling

Model Evaluation (Accuracy, Recall, ROC-AUC)

K-Means Clustering for patient segmentation

Business insights generation

📈 Key Insights

Longer hospital stay and higher medication count increase readmission risk

High-cost patients form a distinct high-risk cluster

Random Forest outperformed Logistic Regression in predictive performance

💼 Business Impact

This model can help hospitals:

Identify high-risk patients before discharge

Reduce avoidable readmissions

Optimize resource allocation
